Start charging (EVCharging := TRUE) only when all these conditions are met:
- An EV is connected (EVConnected = TRUE)
- EV voltage is above the minimum (EVVoltage > MinimumVoltage)
- EV current is at or below the maximum (EVCurrent <= MaximumCurrent)
- EV is not fully charged (EVStateOfCharge < 100.0)
- Charging time has not exceeded the maximum (ChargingTimer <= MaximumChargingTime)

Stop charging (EVCharging := FALSE) if any of these conditions occur:
- EV is disconnected (EVConnected = FALSE)
- EV voltage falls below the minimum (EVVoltage <= MinimumVoltage)
- EV current exceeds the maximum (EVCurrent > MaximumCurrent)
- EV is fully charged (EVStateOfCharge >= 100.0)
- Maximum charging time is exceeded (ChargingTimer > MaximumChargingTime)

Ensure that the charging status is updated based on these conditions at the end of each PLC cycle. Please ensure that the output ST code complies with the syntax rules.The function block should use the following structure:

FUNCTION_BLOCK ChargingStationControl
VAR_INPUT
    EVConnected : BOOL;
    EVVoltage : REAL;
    EVCurrent : REAL;
    EVStateOfCharge : REAL;
    ChargingTimer : TIME;
    MinimumVoltage : REAL;
    MaximumCurrent : REAL;
    MinimumSOC : REAL;
    ChargingVoltage : REAL;
    ChargingCurrent : REAL;
    MaximumChargingTime : TIME;
END_VAR

VAR_OUTPUT
    EVCharging : BOOL;
END_VAR

END_FUNCTION_BLOCK

